snippet: Factors like education, wealth and age may be helping to keep the Garden State’s couples together.
abstract: Field Notes column observes that Census Bureau survey ranks New Jersey as the state with the lowest percentage of residents 18 and older who are divorced; reflects that factors like education, wealth and age may be helping to keep the Garden State's couples together.
lead_paragraph: Factors like education, wealth and age may be helping to keep the Garden State’s couples together.

headline.seo: New Jersey Has Lowest Divorce Rate
headline.main: Want Your Union to Last? Marry in New Jersey
